This paper discusses the potential impact of emerging technologies on healthcare systems, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and healthcare informatics (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the role of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information technology (cs.IT) in enabling this transformation. Finally, the paper touches on the potential social implications of these technologies, which could fall under the category of social and information sciences (cs.SI).
